<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Salenie's Miscellaneous Thoughts on These and Other Abstract Is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></center><!--EZCODE CENTER END-->[/b]<br>
<br>
<br>
1.  Porting for donation.  You get what you get.  A donation is a gift.  I don't care if EQ has turned the meaning of the word to fee.  Fee is fee.  Donation is gift.  Everytime I see &quot;Porting for donations&quot; I am tempted to go to the druid or wizard, say, &quot;port me to XXX&quot; and then aftewards give them a rusty dagger from fishing.  That's my required donation.  No thanks. No bow.  Just their required &quot;donation&quot;.  I never have and never will do this, but I'm tempted.  Hee hee. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2.  Porting for fee.  I have absolutely NO problem with this.  If I hear the shout /porting to all druid locations for 25 plat and I need to go to Toxx I'm estatic!  I give the druid 25 plat, a bow, a gracious thank you, and a mod rod making sure they know what it is if I have the mana.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It is just time and mana.  But then, hey, so is grouping.  I would never deny someone a share of the treasure just because they are only spending time and mana.  That's all most of us spend most of the time (yes, peridots, jaspers, TL components...but 90% of our online expenditure is time and mana).  <br>
<br>
3.  I like all ice cream as long as it doesn't have coconut in it.  Just don't like the grainy texture.  Blech!!<br>
<br>
4.  This specific situation.  Seems to me there is a bit of greed on both side.  Making the poster run to a dangerous place was rude.  Having hostile mobs their was rude and inconsiderate.  Not helping them get a rez was insulting.  Running off before they finished zoning with out even a thank you or helping them regain lost xp or cost of rez because you need to get to a raid is self-centered in the extreme.  Being ticked off that you got nothing when you didn't say explicitly you required a certain amount is silly.  Being ticked off that the portee didn't lift one finger to help you after you died is prefectly reasonable.  Not being ticked off that you were killed cuz it happens in EQ is admirable. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5.  Getting a port.  I will /ooc looking for a port/TL to XXX, will donate.  If I'm really desperate, I will /shout looking for a port/TL to XXX, will donate.  I never do a /who druid/wizard because if I'm shouting and they aren't responding, I figure they are busy.  Think about it.  Druid_2 sees me /ooc.  Druid_2 sees me /ooc again.  Druid_2 sees me /shout.  Druid_2 is gonna suddenly going to go &quot;Oh, I can help Salenie!&quot; just because I /tell them?  FYI:  About 10% of the time I end up running, about 10% I get into a contract negotiation, about 20% of the time I get a &quot;I'll port you for free, come to YYY&quot;, about 60% of the time I get a port for which I end up giving 25-75 plat depending on the porters level, what I have on me, and my mood.<br>
<br>
6.  Port ettiquette.  I really feel for porters.  I think they take a LOT of crapola.  I see this a bit from the side--as a high elf in a robe I obviously can cast clarity (doesn't matter I'm carrying a shovel, in a mage only robe, have a HUGE floating rock next to me, and have been shouting XXth magi LFG).  When I tell people &quot;Wish I could cast clarity!  I'm a magician&quot; they turn around and run off more often then not.  No &quot;Thanks anyway&quot; or &quot;Sorry to bother you&quot;. Hell, I'm lucky to get an &quot;oh.&quot;  This is manners in the 21st century?  Bah!<br>
<br>
So when I get a port, regardless if it is for fee, donation, from a guildee or what have you, the person always gets:  a) a bow, b) a thanks, c) A farewell wish &quot;Safe Journies&quot; &quot;May the All Mother Guide and Protect you&quot;, &quot;May Karanas also blow the wind to your back&quot; or what have you.  If they are of an approriate level for the activity I am porting to (and I'm porting to an activity that takes others...often time I'm moving aorund to do smithing related stuff) I will invite them along. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
7.  Porting for fee.  I have no problem being ported for a fee.  If I need a port, someone charges me for it, and I agree to the contract I'm cool with it.  What ticks me off are taxi's porters that don't realize that they are working for me.  If the contract is &quot;Come to rings and I'll port you for 30 plat&quot; when I show up at rings you damn well better be ready to port me.  If they say, &quot;I'll port you for 30 plat.&quot; then I tell them &quot;Lovely!  I'm at XXX (always same zone).&quot;  This is because you are not doing me a favor....you are not helping me out.  We are in a contract.  You have put yourself out for hire, and I have hired you.  You are currently working for me.  As such I do not wait for you to do one more trade.  I do not wait for you to do a &quot;quick AFK&quot;.  I do not wait for you to do &quot;A couple of friends first.&quot;  You put your services up for sale, and I have purchased them.  I am now your highest priority.  <br>
<br>
Yes, this is a pet peave.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And it so does not apply to anyone else.  Anyone else I will come to you (and I will always ask where you are so I can), I will wait for a few minutes as you wrap something up, and I will donate plat for the ride.  That's because we are not under contract, we are not in a business relationship.  You are doing me a favor.  But as soon as you say, &quot;I will port you for (specific compensation)&quot; it stops being a favor.<br>
<br>
8.  The second season of Buffy the Vampire Slayer was the best.  No other story line was a strong and interesting as the Angel goes bad one.  I liked the mayor a lot!  I liked the maturation of the kids in the first year of college.  I like Dawn as key (and Glory really had some shining moments).  Still on the fence about the new season.  But #2 seems like it will always be the best.<br>
<br>
9.  Druids are a great group class!  I mean c'mon?  Evacs, back up heals, snare, and at the level I'm playing at they have a FR debuff that does damage (Ro's Sundering something or other?) and as most of my DDs are fire based...woohoo!  If I could design the perfect group for KSing in a raid (not that I do that of course...but I can dream) it would be me, a cleric, a druid, and three rogues. Bwhahahahah!<br>
<br>
As an aside, I think every class rocks, IF it is played by a good player of that class.  A good ranger rocks!  A good paladin rocks (I was in a group once that could control aggro to perfection!  He could taunt mobs off the cleric with a flick of the risk, never bitched about taking hits, always stayed on the far side of the mob from my pet)!  Class bashing is silly IMHO.<br>
<br>
10.  Spectre pets are scary.  Maybe I spent too long in Oasis as a teen, but I don't care if the spectre cons indifferently, follows the necro obediently, and is named Jebeker, it still scares me.  Be glad we're not on a PvP server, I'd nuke them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
11.  Clerics charging for rezzes.  Unlike druids and wizards, I WILL /tell a cleric I see in zone that is not /role or /anon on because xp loss sucks!  (Yet another side...my formula for asking is this &quot;Hi!  Can I please get a rez at XXX?&quot;.  Seems rude to me to ask a favor before even saying hello, I will aways say please, and I hate &quot;mah&quot;. What the hell is &quot;mah&quot;?  Yes, I know it is suppose to be me.  bah!!).  If they feel that their time and mana is worth 100 plat, so be it.  I want that rez.  I can just as easily say &quot;Thanks anyway, but I guess I'll just work back that xp the long way.&quot;  I don't because I'd rather go on interesting raids or do smithing than do the xp grind.  Totally worth 50 or 75 or 100 plat to me.  Also, as I will invade their personal space, I think it is perfectly reasonable for them to dictate terms.  They didn't ask to be /tell'ed by me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
12.  Lovebite:  Loved your post!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Would love to see a druid shout:  Porting for pixels, please send tells. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   They would get business from me just for being honest.  Hee hee!<br>
<br>
13.  Clerics who give free rezes because xp loss sucks and they sympathisize rock!!  Clerics who are standing over the body and have their epic weapon and charge are appreciated, but they better never expect any sort of freebie from me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
14.  Dwarkan:  LOL!!!  That is the first post I've seen of yours that made me laugh (much to the amusement of my coworkers...see above).  Thanks. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
15.  EZposts spacing.  Paragraphs are nice.  Punctuation is essential.  If you do nothing else, please at least use periods and reasonable sentance structure.  I can read a really long paragraph...I cannot read a one sentance/55 line post.  :P<br>
