<br>
    I personally only had one character past lvl 9 when I started my druid, and I loved the character.  Now while I don't go around advertising my services, I keep myself non-roleplay / non-anonamous, mostly because I don't really care for those filters.  If someone sends me a tell for a port, chances are I'm not too busy to give it to them, so I'll take them wherever they need to go, provided I can.<br>
<br>
    Now if someone sends you a tell for a port and then expects you to come to them to pick them up, that's plain rude and I may refuse them on that premise depending on my mood at the time.  People who don't pay... well, I never asked them for payment so I have no problem with that.  If they do pay, all the better.<br>
<br>
